how can i transfer movies from my camcorder to my pc via rca cables i have a sony camcorder and want to transfer home movies to my pc i know there are software hardware packages out there to help with this process please provide me with the manufacturer's name there are quite a number of ways you can do it you could use an analogue capture card in your pc and connect the yellow red white rca connections from your camcorder to it and capture direct as mpeg you could use an analogue to usb converter like this http www brickhousesecurity com ad a html and connect it to your pc via usb although i have to say i have never found one of those that works very well you could use a digitiser see here http www simplydv co uk reviews av digitisers html and convert the output from the camcorder to digital and connect to your pc via firewire or if you have a digital camcorder as well quite a few of them check the spec can be used as a digitiser by connecting the vhs to the camera av input and the firewire output to your pc which ever option you choose you will also need some sensible capture and editing software on your computer i would suggest you go and have a look at http www ulead com runme htm Camcorder DVD High-definition television Digital camera Universal Serial Bus 8 mm video format FireWire Musical Instrument Digital Interface IPod DV Digital photography Xbox PlayStation Portable IMac PlayStation 2 Bluetooth Common Unix Printing System Computer hardware PlayStation 3 Digital video Laserdisc Non-linear editing system Apple Macintosh Television Creative Zen Streaming media Integrated Services Digital Broadcasting VHS Digital video recorder Xbox 360 HyperText Transfer Protocol Desktop computer Computer bus Teletext Sound card USB flash drive Digital cinema Warez Digital audio workstation Analog-to-digital converter Software-defined radio Power Mac G4 Cube Floppy disk Oscilloscope Machine vision Charge-coupled device Sound recording Apple Computer Nintendo Revolution MP3 S_